message: Everything I said is accurately sourced.

You're still claiming he has military service... Which he does't. He never had BMQ or anything, he was a cadet while attending a military academy.
As well as students. Just as people training to become commercial pilots are called flight cadets... They still aren't serving the Canadian Forces.

If you read the first line of the officer cadets wiki page that you sent me you would notice it says "Officer Cadet is a rank held by military cadets during their training to become commissioned officers" CADETS! Not officers yet nor serving in the forces
Officer Cadet is a rank held by military cadets during their training to become commissioned officers. <ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cadet</ref>
